<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
    <title>Two-Factor Authentication Enabled</title>
    <style>
      body {
        margin: 0;
        font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
        background-color: #f9fafb;
        color: #111827;
      }
      .container {
        max-width: 1080px;
        margin: 40px auto;
        background: white;
        border-radius: 12px;
        overflow: hidden;
        box-shadow: 0 10px 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
      }
      .header {
        background-color: #0f172a;
        color: #ffffff;
        padding: 24px;
        text-align: center;
      }
      .content {
        padding: 30px;
        text-align: center;
      }
      .content h2 {
        margin-top: 0;
        font-size: 22px;
        font-weight: 600;
      }
      .footer {
        font-size: 12px;
        color: #6b7280;
        text-align: center;
        padding: 20px;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="header">
        <h1>{{health}}</h1>
      </div>
      <div class="content">
        <h2>Two-Factor Authentication Enabled</h2>
        <p>Hello {{to}},</p>
        <p>
          We're letting you know that Two-Factor Authentication (2FA) has been successfully enabled on your account.
        </p>

        <p><strong>Enabled On:</strong> {{date}}</p>

        <p style="margin-top: 20px;">
          If you didn't make this change, please <a href="mailto:omarsamiir@outlook.com" style="color: #3b82f6;">contact support immediately</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="footer">
        &copy; {{year}} {{health}}. All rights reserved.
      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
